subparagraph.text:
serves children
				who have attained the State's legal age for State-funded
				prekindergarten;

has demonstrated
				experience in providing early childhood education services to children;
				and

paragraph.text:
an assurance that
				the State will award subgrants for prekindergarten programs in amounts that are
				sufficient to provide a high-quality prekindergarten experience;

an assurance that
				not less than 25 percent of the qualified prekindergarten providers receiving
				such subgrants will be providers of community-based programs;

a description of
				how the State will ensure that the subgrants are awarded to a wide range of
				types of qualified prekindergarten providers;

a description of
				how the State will meet the needs of the most disadvantaged students, including
				families at or below 200 percent of the poverty line;

a description of
				how the qualified prekindergarten provider will serve eligible children who are
				not served through similar services or programs;

a description of
				a plan for actively involving parents and families in the prekindergarten
				program and the success of their children in the program;

extend part-day
				prekindergarten programs to full-day prekindergarten programs and year-round
				programs;

maintaining a
				maximum class size of 20 children, with at least 1 prekindergarten teacher per
				classroom;

ensuring that the
				ratio of children to prekindergarten teachers and teacher aides shall not
				exceed 10 to 1;

data specifying
				the number and ages of enrolled children, and the family income, race, gender,
				disability, and native language of such children;

program
				evaluation for the purposes of program improvement and parent information;
				or
